  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all five flow-speed operating points, and seven of thirteen credibility factors were formally assessed. Prose review of the evidence package suggests a coherent, well-documented submission with detailed validation narratives, traceable data provenance, and a comprehensive UQ report — features that superficially support a Medium assurance conclusion. However, the achieved credibility level for Model Form falls below the required level for MRL 5, and the decision record nonetheless records an Accepted outcome. This structural inconsistency (W-AR-02) is the planted Critical weakener that, in combination with the Medium assurance declaration, fires COMPOUND-03.",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou2-mrl5-hemolysis",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou2-absolute-hemolysis-below-threshold",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-cfd-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-2023",
